********** What is Angular ? **********

    Angular is a platform and framework for single page applications using HTML and Typescript.
    It is newest form of AngularJS which is developed by Google.
    Angular is open source framework which is used for building mobile and desktop web applications.
    It contains features like Component, Directives, Data Sharing, Data Binding, Observable, Pipes, Forms, HTTPServices, Dependency Injection, Routing etc.
     
     
********** Why Angular ? **********
    Javascript is the most commonly used client-side scripting language. It is written into HTML documents to enable interactions with web pages in many unique ways.
    As a relatively easy-to-learn language with permeating support, it is well-suited to develop modern applications. 
    Angular and Javascript bring structure and consistency to Web Application Development.
    It also provides scalability and maintainability to the user.
    These days, we have a variety of frameworks and libraries designed to provide alternative solutions.
    With respect to front-end web development, Angular addresses many, if not all, of the issues developers face when using JavaScript on its own.
    
    
